The isolate handoff is aiming to rebuild the process tab from this repo, which serves as the oracle for the rewrite repo.

It is reimplementing everything in tiny steps. The handoff files are what I define mostly, but you can make suggestions for the next handoff.

Some of these handoffs will be hints from the oracle for improving processing speed from hard-won results. Be explicit that they're hints and shouldn't be implemented at the cost of breaking things in the new implementation, and they should be benchmarked before and after to see if they're actually an improvement.

## Practices for every handoff

- Keep each handoff to one user-verifiable increment. State the outcome, what is
  explicitly out of scope, and where implementation must stop.
- Treat the rewrite's implemented contracts as the starting point. When older
  handoffs conflict with a newer decision, state the intended precedence without
  discarding unrelated correctness requirements.
- The oracle cannot assume that a forward-looking contract is already
  implemented in the rewrite. Mark unverified rewrite capabilities as
  assumptions or intended behavior, and do not require a new abstraction merely
  because an architecture document anticipates it.
- Before implementation, have the rewrite report where its current types,
  ownership, lifecycle, and supported behavior diverge from the handoff's
  assumptions. Use that report to narrow or adapt the handoff while preserving
  its required outcome; do not force the rewrite to imitate stale oracle shapes.
- Separate required behavior from suggested implementation and from oracle
  hints. Do not let an example command, filename, class layout, or optimization
  become a permanent public contract accidentally.
- Preserve clean ownership boundaries, but do not build speculative frameworks
  for future features. Introduce an abstraction when the current increment
  needs it or when an existing contract already requires it.
- For oracle-derived performance hints, protect correctness first, the handoff should specify to measure the
  rewrite before and after on the same representative inputs, change one
  hypothesis at a time, and retain only demonstrated improvements. Record useful
  negative results.
- Include focused automated tests and a short manual acceptance path. Automated
  success does not substitute for the user's validation of visible interaction.
- Do not continue into the next numbered feature after completing the handoff.

## Accepted benchmark-diagnostic decision

Status: accepted on 2026-07-23.

Reusable benchmarks that help a user estimate responsiveness, runtime,
throughput, or feasibility are product diagnostics, not disposable development
scripts. When a handoff introduces or extends one:

- Put reusable measurement logic in an importable package module and expose it
  through a supported CLI or deliberate UI surface.
- Design useful human output alongside a versioned machine-readable result.
- Report the asset/content identity, source and measured representation, sample
  and cache conditions, median and a tail statistic when supported, the
  software/backend environment, and whether each conclusion is measured,
  extrapolated, or interpreted.
- Keep expensive diagnostics behind explicit user action; do not silently run
  whole-asset work during ordinary startup.
- Keep Qt diagnostics importable within GUI packages and out of headless CLI
  imports. Different layers, such as media service, visible GUI painting, and
  scientific processing, require their own honestly labelled measurements.

Top-level scripts remain appropriate for disposable hypothesis tests, one-time
investigations or migrations, fixture construction, and thin development
launchers whose reusable logic lives in the package. A JSON file in `findings/`
does not by itself make a benchmark a supported product contract.

The accepted initial media surface is:

```powershell
sieve media benchmark ASSET
sieve media benchmark ASSET --native
sieve media benchmark ASSET --json
```

The default measures the same capped display representation used by Isolate;
native-resolution measurement is explicit because it is more expensive and
answers a different question. Media-service results must not claim to measure
GUI painting, overlays, or scientific processing.

## Forward-looking goals

Each increment should remain small while preserving these later capabilities:

- Scientific work is headless and Qt-independent so the same resolved settings
  can eventually run through the GUI, CLI, or HPC execution.
- Large windows and whole assets can use bounded, cancellable streaming rather
  than requiring full-video arrays in memory.
- Asset identity, rational time, media planes, coordinates, validity, coverage,
  and provenance remain explicit at component boundaries.
- Static value filtering and spectral processing are both legitimate paths; do
  not design the common boundary around Morlet or any other single method.
- Stable results can later be consumed by validation, presentation rendering,
  exports, derived children, and stacked detections without making Isolate own
  those consumers.
- Interactive generation tokens and latest-request policy stay in GUI
  orchestration; reusable headless contracts use stable asset/content identity.
- Pixel input ranges remain distinct from downstream output ranges so later
  transforms may request temporal context without changing result ownership.
- Components provide enough stable source and implementation provenance for
  later artifacts to identify their evidence, without prematurely building the
  artifact or pipeline system.
